Privacy Policy for Timely-Tastes

Updated at: 24 November 2025

Timely-Tastes ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your
personal information is collected, used, and disclosed by Timely-Tastes. This Privacy Policy applies to our website,
timelytastes.co.za, and its associated subdomains (collectively, our "Service") alongside our mobile application. By
accessing or using our Service, you signify that you have read, understood, and agree to our collection, storage, use,
and disclosure of your personal information as described in this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service.

1. Information We Collect

Personal Information You Provide:

Account Information: Email address, password (hashed and encrypted)
Order Information: Order details, order status, OTP verification codes
Vendor Information: Shop name, owner name, address, biography, logo/images
Payment Information: Transaction details through our secure payment processor (PayGate)
Listing Information: Product images, descriptions, pricing, availability times
Information Collected Automatically:

Device information and IP addresses
Browser type and version
Usage patterns and interaction with our platform
Order history and preferences
Location data (for finding nearby vendors)
2. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

To create and manage your account
To process orders and facilitate food collections
To verify your identity using OTP systems
To process payments securely
To connect customers with local food vendors
To improve our platform and user experience
To communicate order updates and service information
To prevent fraud and ensure platform security
To calculate vendor ratings and reviews
To display available food listings with accurate timing
3. Data We Process Based on Your Role

For Customers:

Email address
Order history and preferences
Transaction records
OTP verification data
Collection locations and times
For Vendors:

Business information (name, address, owner details)
Shop logo and biography
Food listing details and images
Pricing and inventory information
Performance ratings and reviews
Sales and transaction data
4. Payment Processing

We use PayGate as our third-party payment processor. We do not store your full credit card details on our servers. All
payment information is encrypted and processed securely through PayGate's compliant payment infrastructure.

5. Data Storage and Security

Location: Data is stored on secure servers located in South Africa
Encryption: We use SSL encryption for all data transmissions
Access Control: Strict access controls limit who can view your personal information
OTP Security: One-time passwords are generated securely and have limited validity periods
Vendor Images: Shop logos and food images are stored securely and only displayed as intended
6. Data Retention

We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide our services and fulfill the purposes described
in this policy:

Active Accounts: Data retained while your account remains active
Order History: Maintained for 6 years for business records and customer service
Vendor Information: Retained while vendors remain active on our platform
Transaction Records: Kept for 5 years as required by South African financial regulations
Inactive Accounts: Deleted after 2 years of inactivity
7. Your Rights Under POPIA (Protection of Personal Information Act)

As a South African company, we comply with POPIA and you have the right to:

Access your personal information we hold
Request correction of inaccurate information
Object to processing of your personal information
Request deletion of your personal information
File a complaint with the Information Regulator
8. Sharing of Information

We may share your information with:

Vendors: Necessary order information to fulfill your food collections
Payment Processors: PayGate for transaction processing
Service Providers: Hosting, analytics, and customer support services
Legal Authorities: When required by South African law or legal process
We do not sell your personal information to third parties.

9. International Data Transfers

While we primarily store data in South Africa, some service providers may process data internationally. We ensure
adequate protection through contracts and security measures.

10. Cookies and Tracking

We use cookies and similar technologies to:

Remember your login sessions
Personalize your experience
Analyze platform usage
Prevent fraud
11. Children's Privacy

Our services are not directed to individuals under 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

12. Vendor Responsibilities

Vendors on our platform are responsible for:

Ensuring they have lawful basis for processing customer data
Maintaining accurate business information
Securing any customer data they receive through orders
Complying with POPIA requirements
13. Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. We will notify you of significant changes through our platform or email.

14. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your personal information, please contact us:

Via Email: privacy@timelytastes.co.za
Via Phone: [Your Contact Number]
Via Address: [Your Physical Address in South Africa]
Information Officer: [Name of Information Officer]
For POPIA-related requests, you may also contact the South African Information Regulator.

15. Governing Law

This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of South Africa, particularly the Protection of Personal Information Act
(POPIA) No. 4 of 2013. *@








